org.orgName: District Court of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory

body.p: IN THE DISTRICT COURT, Of the Third Judicial District of Washington Territory, holding terms at Seattle, for the County of King.
The People of the United States of America, to the Sheriff of King County Greeting:

We command you, that you have the body of Thomas Kerr by you imprisoned and detained as it is said, together with the time and cause of such imprisonment and detention, by whatsoever name said Thomas Kerr shall be called or charged, by the HON. RICHARD A. JONES Thomas Burke, Judge of the aforesaid court in the court room of the said court in the City of Seattle W.T. on the 9th day of Feby 1889 at 4 o'clok P.M. of said day to do and receive what shall then and there be considered concerning him the said Thomas Kerr And have you then and there this writ.
WITNESS THE HON. RICHARD A. JONES Thomas Burke, Judge of said District Court, and the seal thereof this 9th day of February A.D. 1889
W.E. Ledgerwood, Clerk. By. H.T. Harmon, Deputy Clerk.
In the District Court, Third Judicial District, Holding terms at Seattle, W.T.
In the Matter of the Application of Thomas Kerr For Writ of Habeas Corpus.
Returned and filed this 9th day of Feby A.D. 1889
W.E. Ledgerwood Clerk. By H.T. Harmon Deputy Clerk.
